Step 1: Identify the relevant numbers.
• From the balance sheet, the current assets at period‐end is 20,314,894.50.
• From the income statement, the Total Revenue (or Main Business Revenue) is 20,318,450.67.

Step 2: Calculate the Current Assets Turnover Ratio.
One common method is to use end-of‐period current assets:
  Ratio = (Total Revenue) ÷ (Current Assets End Amount)
    = 20,318,450.67 ÷ 20,314,894.50
    ≈ 1.00002
Rounded to two decimal places, the ratio is 1.00.
